On Feb. 14 Whittington suffered a setback when a shotgun pellet penetrated his heart. His worsened condition focused attention on the unanswered questions: Whose fault and why the delay in reporting? In Texas a sheriff's office cleared Cheney of any wrongdoing. On the question of delay, Bush's staff deferred to Cheney's and Cheney's to their Texas hosts. On Feb. 15 Cheney broke his silence in a Fox News interview, accepting full-blame for the shooting, but defending his decision to leave the reporting of the incident to the owner of the ranch where it occurred. 